Summary 02 of the book of Christian theology:

Nowadays, the meaning of the word orthodoxy and heresy has been changed a lot. Orthodoxy may be used as the antonym of heresy, or the church of Russia or Greek, or the movement inside Protestantism in the first 17th century. In the early church, the word of "Orthodoxy" was used as the antonym of "Heresy" mainly. 

In the early church, there are many concepts existed, and some of them were doubted afterward, thus to define the right ones among those early concepts, the word "orthodoxy" was used in Roman Catholic. However, according the Bauer, in that age, the principle of what can be thought as orthodoxy was defined by Roman Catholic, and they were using their superior power to attack other teachings by pointing others as "heresy". 

The opinion of Bauer was criticized a lot and we are not sure how long can this opinion exists, but we cannot deny that there were indeed some concepts existed in early age were eliminated afterward. Although such elimination existed, we shall devote ourselves to research the main topics in our belief. 

Those debates are not belong to the ancient time only, but also to this age, even in today, it's important for us all. The definition of Schleiermacher points that "heresy is a thing that having the appearance of Christianity but a contrary essence."  The word heresy was abused in many places, but it's still a necessary concept in theology. 

The core point of Schleiermacher is: God saved us through Jesus Christ only, neither any other figures nor other ways. Whoever deny this point is denying the fundamental truth of Christianity, and not belonging to the Christianity. Heresy is not among unbeliever, but among believers who believe in a wrong way. 

There are four heresies exist according the Schleiermacher: the first one is Ebionitism, who was denying the superior existence of Jesus Christ; the second one is Docetism, who was thinking the body of Christ was just a phantasm and cannot save us; the third one is Pelagianism, who was denying the predestination and relying on the efforts of human; the fourth is Manichaeism, who was thinking that humanity cannot response the salvation inside Christ. 

Beside heresy, another issue is the relationship between Christianity and secular culture. According to Emil Brunner, culture  is the "materialization of meaning". 

In the second century, there was a thinker called Justinus, he thought we should use those secular culture as a tool to preach the Gospel, according to his words, the world is sowing by the seed of godly wisdom, thus once we get to know this point, we can use those culture freely. Although his words was important, there were rarely some ones agree with him. There were even some ones thought those secular culture deceived all mans and disdained the truth. 

Tertullianus disagree with Justinus, he criticized him fiercely, he thinks Christianity should be far away with such secular culture, to keep it's identity. According to his words, Christianity will become a culture movement to refuse any other culture to avoid being polluted. But after 313 AD, when 	Constantine converted to a believer of Christianity, the culture of Christianity became the main culture of Roman Empire, then, how to deal with the relationship between Christianity and other cultures in the world? 

Augustine of Hippo has given us his answer, that "receiving secular culture critically".  In his opinion, the status is like the age when Israel exodus from Egypt, they excluded the golden or silver idols of Egypt, but bring the golden and silver jewels of Egypt, and then, after they using those golden and silver jewels to make an idol like gentiles, God taught them how to use those golden and silver jewels, that's to use those things for his temple, which means, the temple of his spirit. Thus the jewels can be used for a good thing, a noble thing, that's not any idols, but the only One God. 
当时的偶像也是金银的啊。金银做的偶像不能带走，但金银的首饰可以，只是，金银首饰仍然可以被用来做偶像。太可怕了。就像今天，玛门神不能侍奉，但生活是可以用玛门买些用的，只是，这些能被卖掉做成玛门神。所以，是卖掉玛门换成用的，还是卖掉用的换成玛门神呢？
Thus the skills of thinking, writing, even speaking were  released from idolatry, and now they are serving the Gospel. The thinking of Augustine became the primary thinking of Western Churches, using any thing can be used to preach the Gospel. 
但应该是已经存在的，神已经给的，而不是自己去弄一些自己可以享受的，努力为此，然后说是为了神。比如该隐，努力弄的，也是服侍神，但是，有问题。以色列人用的，是神直接给的，不是偶像，是可用的。自己努力挣的金银首饰给神不更好吗？是啊，如果是为了这个目的侍奉金银的神像好得一些金银好能献给神，神会高兴吗？而且，神确实是，对比之下已经是属于次要的了，因为，我们首先能满足自己的欲望，如同该隐。如果不为满足自己的欲望，如同亚伯，一点不是为自己欲望的放羊，献给神，这其中，神真不是次要的，因为，没有对比的，神是唯一的。他是一。
When it was 20th century, Nibo proposed five paradigms of "Christianity and culture": the first one is against culture, the second one is belonging to culture, the third one is above the culture, the fourth one is being paradoxical with culture, the fifth one is changing the culture. Although his opinion was criticized a lot, it's still an useful thing for theological references. 

The opinion of Hippo is a bright viewpoint, but it encourage western believers to serve money to offer money. Maybe it's used in many other regions, because it's a good intention, at least in appearance. One important thing we should notice in the exodus of Israel is that: the golden or silver jewels was given by God, not by their serving golden or silver idols. Can we serve idols to get gold or silver to offer to God? Will God enjoy our efforts? Is our intention is JUST for God? 

Cain work hardly to make food to offer to God, but meanwhile, Cain need those food first, God second. There are many things in the world, sometimes we like those things, but we need a pretext to glorify our selfish intention, by offering the things to God, like Cain. Serving God is not enough, serving God ONLY is the most important principle. For Yahweh is our God, Yahweh is ONE. HE is ONE. 




